<body style="font-size:16pt;font-family:serif;color:white;" background="IMAGE_PLACEHOLDER">

<h1><u>Basics</u></h1>

<p><b>
Lasertag3D is a multi-player game of laser tag where gravity is optional.
The object of the game is to get the most points by shooting other players and not getting shot yourself.
   For each hit made, you gain 3 points, and for each hit taken, you lose 1.
</b></p>
<p><b>To shoot, click where you want to shoot.
  You can only shoot 2 beams per second.
</b></p>
<p><b>When you hit someone or are hit, you will hear a noise and a message will appear in your sidebar telling you what happened.
</b></p>

</body>
</html>

--------

<!-- Help text, page 2 -->
<html>
<body style="font-size:16pt;font-family:serif;color:white;" background="IMAGE_PLACEHOLDER">

<h1><u>Movement</u></h1>

<p><b>
To move, use the following controls:
<br />
<ul>
 <li>Mouse movement -- Rotate</li>
 <li>'W' -- Move forwards</li>
 <li>'S' -- Move backwards</li>
 <li>'A' key -- Strafe left</li>
 <li>'D' key -- Strafe right</li>
 <li>'Ctrl' -- Increase the speed of all other keys</li>
</ul>
</b></p>
<p><b>
In scenes where there is no gravity (such as the mazes), you can use these additional controls:
<br />
<ul align="left">
 <li>'Space' -- Strafe up</li>
 <li>'Shift' -- Strafe down
 <li>'Q' key or center mouse button -- Rotate counter-clockwise</li>
 <li>'E' key or right mouse button -- Rotate clockwise</li>
</ul>
</b></p>
<p><b>
You can change these key settings at any time be going into Personalization and choosing the "Key Bindings" tab.
</b></p>

</body>
</html>

--------

<!-- Help text, page 3 -->
<html>
<body style="font-size:16pt;font-family:serif;color:white;" background="IMAGE_PLACEHOLDER">

<h1><u>Explore</u></h1>

<p><b>
There are two different game modes accessable from the main menu: Explore (single-player) and Lasers+People (multi-player).
</b></p>
<p><b>
In Explore mode, you are by yourself exploring a scene.
  This is useful for learning the controls and learning about the scenes.
  Additionally, if you choose a maze scene, you are basically in a graphically enhanced version of the game
 <a href="http://www.mattweidner.com/Maze3D/">Maze3D</a>.
</b></p>

</body>
</html>

--------

<!-- Help text, page 4 -->
<html>
<body style="font-size:16pt;font-family:serif;color:white;" background="IMAGE_PLACEHOLDER">

<h1><u>Lasers+People</u></h1>
<p><b>
In Lasers+People mode, you can play with other people through the Internet.
  After you click on this menu option, you will see several tabs.
  Each tab is named after a scene; each scene's tab contains a list of all the games that people are trying to start in that scene.
  You can join someone else's game, get information about other games, or start your own.
</b></p>
<p><b>If you want to find the ping from your computer to a certain game's server, you must select the game and then press the "Ping Server" button.
  After a second or so, the ping (in milliseconds) will show up in the selected game's description.
  During a game, the ping will show itself as the time between when you do something (move, shoot, etc.) and when you see its effects.  Lower is better.
</b></p>
<p><b>If you create or join a game that is taking a while to start because not enough players are joining, use the "Request Start" button to request that the game starts with the players you have so far.
  The other players who already joined will be asked if they want to start or not; once enough of them approve/disapprove, either the game will start or you will be told that your request was rejected.
  A 2/3 majority is required for a start request to be accepted.
</b></p>

</body>
</html>

