<!-- Help text, page 5 -->
<html>
<body style="font-size:16pt;font-family:serif;color:white;" background="IMAGE_PLACEHOLDER">

<h1><u>Settings</u></h1>
<p><b>
The settings are grouped into 3 tabs: General, Key Bindings, and Network.
</b></p>
<p><b>
The General tab lets you set your screen name, the field of view, and the mouse sensitivity.
<br />  Your screen name is the name that others will see when joining or playing in multi-player games.
<br />  The field of view controls how wide your virtual sight is, in degrees.
  Higher values let you see more, but they also distort the view slightly.
  Lower values show more detail but let you see less.
  The default value of 90 degrees is the most realistic looking.
<br />  The mouse sensitivity controls how quickly you rotate.
</b></p>
<p><b>
The Key Bindings tab is self-explanatory.
</b></p>
<p><b>
The Network tab is for configuring your computer to host multiplayer games.
</b></p>

</body>
</html>

